25|$|Though {{most of the}} Constitution's framers {{supported}} the right of individual States to regulate alcohol, some - such as Richard O'Connor - believed Section 113 to be unnecessary because the States would already have this power despite Section 92. Furthermore, O'Connor was concerned that by the specific inclusion of Section 113 (and Section 112), the <b>police</b> <b>power</b> of the States {{would be limited to}} the powers which were specifically enumerated.|$|E
